3 But this kind of punishment cannot extend as far as death, ex- cept in what they call a reductive way, in which negations are reduced to the opposite class. For as Christ said, it would have been better for some if they had never been born, that is not so ill: so for in- curable dispositions, it is better, that is less evil, to die than to live, since by living they are sure to become worse. Seneca says they must perish, in order that they may not perish, So Jamblichus, Plutarch, Galen.
